# Security+ PBQ / drag-and-drop template

When adding or editing **Security+ performance-based drag-and-drop** pages, build new scenarios in **`public/COMP_TIA_SEC+/SEC+_Sim_Hot_Spot/PBQ_Production/{scenario-slug}/`** (one folder per scenario, noindex), then ship published HTML in **`public/COMP_TIA_SEC+/SEC+_PBQ/`**. Legacy patterns: **`SEC+_Sim_Hot_Spot/pending/`**. Do not use `SEC+_Questions/` or root `public/question-*.html`.

**Production layout:** One HTML page per scenario — **`PBQ_Production/{scenario-slug}/{scenario-slug}.html`** — with folder sidebar + exhibit modals (`pbq-folder-suite.js`). Discovery is via **`SEC+_Training_Portal.html`** (no PBQ hub index). Edit **`{scenario-slug}/sections/{section-id}.html`**, then **`npm run build:pbq-suite`**. Legacy `*-partN.html` → `{slug}/{slug}.html#section-id`.

## Copy from

| Layout | Reference page | Use when |
|--------|----------------|----------|
| **Map / categories** | `security-control-map.html` | Tokens → labeled drop zones (layers, zones, roles) |
| **Ordered timeline** | `log-timeline-forensics.html` | Tokens → numbered sequence slots |
| **Skeleton** | `TEMPLATE-dragdrop.html` | Placeholders + checklist |

**Shared assets (do not duplicate inline styles):**

- `/css/bcc-question-link-nav.css` — Back / Home / Next link buttons
- `/COMP_TIA_SEC+/SEC+_Samples/secplus-sample-touch.css` — touch targets, watermark base
- `/COMP_TIA_SEC+/js/secplus-sim-page.css` — white sim page chrome (same family as `simulation-*.html`)
- `/COMP_TIA_SEC+/js/secplus-pbq-page.css` — PBQ chrome; **`.pbq-bct-sim`** aligns with BCT simulation style

**BCT simulation pattern** (`PBQ_Production/` build): match `PBQ_Production/dark-web-account-protection/dark-web-account-protection.html` — `Simulation:` H1, `.lead` + `.instructions` card, blue exhibit tiles (`#005ecb`), bordered `.sim-frame` / `.panel`, BCT blue action buttons. Body: `secplus-sim-page secplus-pbq-ui pbq-bct-sim`.

**Deep dive:** vault `marketing-vault/SEC+/PBQ/{slug}/deep-dive-solution.md` → `secplus-pbq-deep-dive-data.js` via `npm run build:pbq-suite`. Footer button **Deep dive explanation** at the bottom of each scenario page opens modal.

